<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-01-28T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-01-28T14:00:00-05:00" n="887" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d887">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 861.00/1014</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Minister in Sweden</hi> (<persName corresp="#p_MIN1" type="from"><hi rend="italic">Morris</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Stockholm</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-01-28T20:00:00+01:00"><hi rend="italic">January
                                            28, 1918, 8 p.m.</hi></date>
                                    <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received January 29, 9.58
                                    a.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>1389. Have just seen Minister for Foreign Affairs who informed me
                                that Finnish government had notified Swedish representative in
                                Helsingfors that it could not longer be responsible for lives of
                                Swedish subjects and Swedish representative has left Helsingfors on
                                special train. Viborg is entirely in the hands of Bolsheviks,
                                Helsingfors soon will be, and St. Petersburg Bolsheviks have
                                promised assistance. He added that Swedish delegate was watching
                                internal situation closely, fearing spread of Bolshevik propaganda
                                in Sweden.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed><persName corresp="#p_MIN1"><hi rend="smallcaps">Morris</hi></persName></signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>